               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office prayers and litanies (fols. 4ra-17ra)
 II) Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse "Ordinary of the Mass" (fols. 17ra-36va)
 III) Anaphoras (fols.
                     36va-141vb )
 III-1) Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols.
                     36va-52vb)
 III-2) Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols.
                     53ra-62vb)
 III-3) Anaphora of St John, son of Thunder (fols.
                     62vb-71vb)
 III-4) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of Nicaea (fols.
                     71vb-79va)
 III-5) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom (fols. 79va-84va)
                     III-6) Anaphora of St Dioscorus of Alexandria (fols. 84va-87ra)
 III-7)
                     Anaphora of St Epiphanius of Cyprus (fols. 87rb-92va)
 III-8) Anaphora of
                     St Athanasius of Alexandria (fols. 92va-102va)
 III-9) Anaphora of St
                     Gregory of Armenia ("Hosanna-liturgy of St Gregory") (fols. 102va-108rb)
                     III-10) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols. 108rb-114rb)
 III-11) Anaphora
                     of St Cyril of Alexandria (fols. 114rb-120rb)
 III-12) Anaphora of St Basil
                     of Caesarea (fols. 120rb-126rb)
 III-13) Second Anaphora of St Gregory
                     ("Christmas-liturgy of St Gregory") (fols. 127va-129rb)
 
 Additiones
                     1-2.</summary>
