                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>The scribe is possibly the same as the one
                        of the Ms. GMG-019.<date>late 19th- early 20th century</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይበል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይበል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                           <item>በእ፡ for በእንተ፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይበል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the king, bishop and
                           patriarch; groups of red lines alternating with black in the incipit page
                           of Text I; incipits of the texts and their sections; incipit of Additio
                           1; musical notation signs; (abbreviated) directives for the ministers;
                           some other words, e.g. yǝtǝfeśaḥǝ, ṣägahu, ṣällǝyu,kāʿǝba; elements of
                           the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
