                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0113NSM">Nǝḥbi Qǝddus Mikāʾel / NSM</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1876" notAfter="1913">King Mǝnilǝk II (r. 1844-1913) is
                        mentioned on <locus target="#3ra">3ra</locus>; The Coptic Patriarch Cyril
                        (in tenure 1875-1927) and Metropolitan Ṗeṭros (in tenure 1881-1917) are
                        mentioned on <locus target="#2vb">2vb</locus>, 27rb, 30rb.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>The original donor appears to be Walda
                     Samāʿt. His name and names of his family members are mentioned in the
                     supplication formula on 38vb. 
 Other names
                     have been inserted in supplication formulas throughout the Ms. with recent
                     hand, in red pen. Bayru Yäšǝqa (?) is mentioned in Additio
                     2.</provenance></history>
